{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-commit Validation & Commit",
  "description": "Runs pre-commit hooks, generates an HTML commit report under .kiro/html/, shows the report path, and asks user to confirm before committing.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Files have been modified. Please follow this workflow:\n\n1. Run `pre-commit run --all-files` to validate all changes\n2. If pre-commit fails:\n   - Analyze the failures and attempt to fix them automatically\n   - Run pre-commit again to verify fixes\n   - If fixes cannot be applied automatically, explain the issues to the user and ask how to proceed\n3. Once pre-commit passes successfully:\n   - Review all staged and unstaged changes using `git status` and `git diff`\n   - Analyze the changes to determine a commit message following conventional commit format\n\n4. **Generate an HTML commit report** before committing:\n   - Create the directory `.kiro/html/` if it doesn't exist\n   - Generate a filename using the format: `YYYYMMDDhhmm-committitle.html` where:\n     - `YYYYMMDDhhmm` is the current date/time (e.g., 202605101430)\n     - `committitle` is the commit title slugified (lowercase, spaces replaced with dashes, special chars removed)\n   - The HTML page must be a self-contained, well-styled document (use inline CSS, dark theme preferred) containing:\n     a. **Commit Message**: The full commit title and description\n     b. **Files Changed**: List of all files modified/added/deleted with their status (M/A/D) and lines added/removed stats\n     c. **Pages Affected**: Based on the file-to-route mapping below, list which frontend pages at http://localhost:5173/ are likely affected by this commit, with clickable links:\n        - `frontend/src/pages/HomePage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/monitoring.ts` → http://localhost:5173/\n        - `frontend/src/pages/InventoryPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/inventory.ts` → http://localhost:5173/inventory\n        - `frontend/src/pages/ExecutionsPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/executions.ts` or `backend/src/routes/commands.ts` → http://localhost:5173/executions\n        - `frontend/src/pages/NodeDetailPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/facts.ts` → http://localhost:5173/nodes/:id\n        - `frontend/src/pages/PuppetPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/puppet.ts` or `backend/src/routes/hiera.ts` or `backend/src/routes/puppetHistory.ts` → http://localhost:5173/puppet\n        - `frontend/src/pages/GlobalJournalPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/journal.ts` → http://localhost:5173/journal\n        - `frontend/src/pages/UserManagementPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/users.ts` → http://localhost:5173/users\n        - `frontend/src/pages/GroupManagementPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/groups.ts` → http://localhost:5173/groups\n        - `frontend/src/pages/RoleManagementPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/roles.ts` → http://localhost:5173/roles\n        - `frontend/src/pages/ProvisionPage.svelte` → http://localhost:5173/provision\n        - `frontend/src/pages/IntegrationSetupPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/integrations.ts` → http://localhost:5173/integrations/:integration/setup\n        - `frontend/src/pages/IntegrationConfigPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/config.ts` → http://localhost:5173/integrations/config\n        - `frontend/src/pages/LoginPage.svelte` or `backend/src/routes/auth.ts` → http://localhost:5173/login\n        - `backend/src/routes/tasks.ts` → http://localhost:5173/executions\n        - `backend/src/routes/packages.ts` → http://localhost:5173/nodes/:id (packages tab)\n        - `backend/src/routes/playbooks.ts` → http://localhost:5173/executions\n        - `backend/src/routes/streaming.ts` → http://localhost:5173/executions\n        - `backend/src/middleware/*` or `backend/src/services/*` → All pages (infrastructure change)\n        - `backend/src/database/*` → All pages (data layer change)\n        - `frontend/src/components/*` → Infer from component name which pages use it\n        - `frontend/src/lib/*` → All pages (shared library change)\n     d. **What to Check**: Based on the affected pages and the nature of the changes, provide specific testing guidance (e.g., \"Verify inventory table loads correctly\", \"Check that SSH execution streaming still works\")\n     e. **Impact Analysis**: Use `kirograph_impact` or reasoning about the changed symbols to describe the blast radius. Mention if the change is isolated or cross-cutting.\n     f. **Codebase Stats**: Number of files changed, total lines added/removed, which workspaces are affected (frontend/backend/both), which integrations are touched\n   - Write the HTML file to `.kiro/html/YYYYMMDDhhmm-committitle.html`\n\n5. **Show the report path** to the user:\n   - Display: \"📋 Commit report generated: `.kiro/html/<filename>.html`\"\n   - Provide a clickable file link so the user can open it in the browser\n\n6. **Ask the user to confirm** they want to proceed with the commit. Wait for explicit confirmation.\n\n7. Only after user confirms:\n   - Stage all changes with `git add .` (excluding the .kiro/html/ report itself if desired, but it's fine to include it)\n   - Create the commit with `git commit -m \"title\" -m \"detailed description\"`\n   - Confirm the commit was successful\n\nFollow git best practices for commit messages:\n- Use conventional commit format: type(scope): description\n- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore\n- Keep first line under 50 characters\n- Use imperative mood\n- Include detailed body explaining what changed and why"
  }
}
